To solve for the arithmetic average, we can simply take the sum of all the values and divide it by the number of years. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Arithmetic average}&=\dfrac{\text{Sum of the values}}{\text{number of years}}
\end{aligned}$$

Substituting the given values, we will get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Arithmetic average}&=\dfrac{8+26+14-17+31-1}{6}
\end{aligned}$$
